Each action has the following properties:

•	"ActionNumber": An representing the sequence number of the action.
•	"ActionName": Action Name.
•	"Product": A string specifying the product associated with the action.
•	"Rules": An array of objects representing the conditions that must be met for a rule to satisfied to create a SAP action. Mininum one rule needs to be satisfied to generate a SAP action. These rules are applied against event data received from Penrose. Each rule object has following properties
      * "Conditions": An array of objects representing the conditions that must be met for the rule to be satisfied. Each condition object has following properties.
            * "AttributeDataType" (a string specifying the data type of the attribute),
            * "AttributeName" (a string specifying the name of the attribute in received event JSON),
            * "AttributeValue" (a string specifying the value of the attribute).
•	"Attributes": An array of objects representing the attributes associated with the action. Each attribute object has following properties
      * "IsRequired" (a boolean indicating whether the attribute is required),
      * "Section" (the section to which the attribute belongs),
      * "JsonPropertyName" (the name of the attribute in event JSON payload),
      * "XmlNodeName" (the name of the attribute in SAP XML payload),
      * "SortingOrder" (an integer specifying the sorting order of the attribute).
*/

